comment_regular_data.body: Is it failing due to internal issues in travis/project configuration?

It's failing because our builds and tests depend on a lot of things that can fail:
- Every http request can fail (apt-get, opam, and cabal all make lots of them). If any one of them fails, there is no retry logic and the build fails.
- Tox tests can fail easily, because they build a small local network and expect no interference. Small tox networks are quite sensitive to other tox instances appearing and disappearing quickly.
- Docker can fail to fetch images.
- Travis can arbitrarily fail for various reasons (bad image rollout interacting with something they didn't test).

In this case, it looks like there is an issue with Travis. Restarting a previously green build (from master) now [fails reproducibly](https://travis-ci.org/TokTok/c-toxcore/jobs/174373907). I'd suggest we wait for a bit. If Travis doesn't restore operations within a day or two, I'll contact them about it.

In the meantime, can you squash the two commits? It would also be good to make a slightly more descriptive PR title, and make the commit title match the PR title. These will end up in the autogenerated changelog.

"Now it compiles under `-Werror`" seems misleading: https://travis-ci.org/TokTok/c-toxcore/jobs/174656110#L1364 - clearly it does compile under `-Werror`, because we have that flag enabled on Travis. Can you clarify that?

_[testing/av_test.c, line 808 at r2](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/260#-KWFZ_67gFGU4Ug56gyO:-KWFZ_67gFGU4Ug56gyP:b-4pxc7x) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/c-toxcore/blob/c4ddbb787fe9c4d9c0fc9bdf49bd21ec0f5bfd9e/testing/av_test.c#L808)):_

> ``` C
>     Pa_Terminate();
> 
>     (void)video_frame_duration;
> ```

I'm not a fan of this. It silences a completely valid warning: we have a command line option that is not used. We should be warned about this, so we don't forget. If you insist on silencing this warning, please move it to the assignment (line 467). By itself, this void statement makes no sense, and there is no comment explaining it.

 cmake .

```

)

The thing is av_test.c will be included in build only if opencv & sndfile & portaudio libs installed, otherwise it is just silently ignored. ( CMakeLists.txt line 462 )

And when it included 
`make` fails with
`c-toxcore/testing/av_test.c:439:13: error: variable ‘video_frame_duration’ set but not used [-Werror=unused-but-set-variable]`

Travis is ok now. The current failure is temporary. I've restarted the build. I've also invited @vassad and @Mikhael-Danilov to join the toktok org. For future contributions, you can restart the build yourself if you think it's a temporary failure. Examples of temporary failures are:
- Timeouts
- HTTP errors
- Use-after-free bugs in toxav tests (this is a known low priority race condition)
